 (5593,126,483,'Violin',4824,'Instruction in violin at the advanced undergraduate and graduate level. Music majors must register concurrently in MUS 250. May be repeated to a maximum of 12 hours. 2 or 3 undergraduate hours, or 2 or 4 graduate hours. (Summer session, 1 or 2 undergraduate or graduate hours.) Prerequisite: Primarily for music majors; junior standing. Passing of an audition is required prior to initial registration in any applied music course as approved by the faculty of the appropriate applied music division.'),
 (5594,126,484,'Viola',4825,'Instruction in viola at the advanced undergraduate and graduate level. Music majors must register concurrently in MUS 250. May be repeated to a maximum of 12 hours. 2 or 3 undergraduate hours, or 2 or 4 graduate hours. (Summer session, 1 or 2 undergraduate or graduate hours.) Prerequisite: Primarily for music majors; junior standing. Passing of an audition is required prior to initial registration in any applied music course as approved by the faculty of the appropriate applied music division.');
